Warning
FCDO advises against all but essential travel to Bangladesh.

The Foreign, Commonwealth & Development Office (FCDO) provides advice about risks of travel to help British nationals make informed decisions. Find out more about FCDO travel advice.
FCDO advises against all but essential travel to the whole of Bangladesh
Your travel insurance could be invalidated if you travel against FCDO advice. Consular support is also severely limited where FCDO advises against travel.
Violence at Protests
There are widespread protests across cities in Bangladesh. There are numerous rallies planned for 19 July 2024. You are advised to shelter in a safe place and follow the advice of local authorities. 
Communications have been severely disrupted, including mobile signal, internet access and local television signals.
Many of the ongoing protests across Bangladesh have turned violent and there have been deaths. Dhaka international airport is currently experiencing operational difficulties and there have been severe interruptions to communications making it difficult for people to understand how to avoid demonstrations.
